<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <link href='/stylesheets/bootstrap.min.css' rel="stylesheet">
    <link href="https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.0.6/css/all.css" rel="stylesheet">
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/bootstrap-social.css' />
    <link rel='stylesheet' href='/stylesheets/style.css' />
    <title>Skry</title>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="topBar">
        <a href="/"><h2 class="title">Skry</h2></a>
        <% if(!logged){%>
            <a href="/auth/facebook" id="icon" class="btn-social btn-facebook" ><span class="fab fa-facebook-square"></span>Log in with Facebook</a>
            <!-- <a href="/auth/instagram" ><button class="btn-social-icon btn-instagram"><span class="fab fa-instagram"></span></button></a> -->
        <%} else {%>
            <a href="/user">
                <img class="profilePic" src=<%=user.picPath%>
                 </a>
                 <span>Welcome <%=user.provider_name%></span>
            <a href="/logout"><p class="logout">Logout</p></a>
        <% } %>
    </div>
    <div class="login-container">
        <div>
            <a href="/auth/facebook" id="icon" class="btn-social btn-facebook" ><span class="fab fa-facebook-square"></span>Log in with Facebook</a>
        </div>
        <br>
        <p><strong>Why can I only log in with Facebook?</strong></p>
        <p>We believe it's important that every update and review in our app is legitimate. <br>
            Limiting the update/review feature to Facebook users helps us do just that. <br>
            It lets us put a face and a name to each review, so you know a real person is behind them. <br>
            If you don't have a Facebook account you won't be able to upload photos, or review each club, <br>
            but you can still browse and see everybody else's reviews and photos.
        </p>
    </div>
</body>

</html>

